Rating: 4
Following other reviews, I omitted the chicken wings and cut the lemon juice in half. I did not have lemon oil so used olive oil only cut that back to 1/4 cup. I baked the marinated thighs in a clay pot, with a lid surrounded by large pieces of potato and sweet potato, rubbed with the marinade at 375 for 45 minutes. The thighs I used were bone-in and skin on so I removed the lid and broiled the dish until the skin was browned and crispy. So easy and delicious. I am making it again tonight for a ladies get-together.

