Rating: 3
This was delicious! I made a few changes and substitutions that I think brought it home: 1. Cilantro instead of mint--this was incredible. 2. Chose the olive oil over the lemon oil--it would have been WAY too lemony otherwise. 3. Added one extra garlic clove, as well as some crushed red peppers and chili powder, just for a little spice. 4. Put in an extra 1/2 teaspoon of the cumin. The only thing I would do differently next time is the lemon zest. About a third of the required lemon I would actually zest with a zester. The other two thirds I would again use the peeler, but then chop up the pieces a bit more. Otherwise the pieces of zest you get are sometime too large. A great dish!

