Rating: 4
I used this recipe as a guide rather than following it exactly, and the result is a very tender and flavorful dish that always gets lots of compliments. When I make it, I use LOTS more garlic - an entire bulb of pressed garlic. I double the spices (esp the cumin), and add red pepper, and use one lemon for juice and zest. I make it with a cut-up whole chicken, and shove the chunky stuff under the skin, and rub the outsides of the chickens with the remaining mixture. It's messy, but worth it. Then I grill the chickens on a covered charcoal grill for about an hour. It goes well with a greek salad of tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion, olive, feta and olive oil. This is a nice combo because you can do all of your prep ahead of time. I don't even turn the chickens. After you put the them on the grill, you can sit back and relax with a glass of wine until your guests arrive!

